      <body>Updated the docs for ActiveRecord#first and #last.  Example for #first below.

# A convenience wrapper for &lt;tt&gt;find(:first, *args)&lt;/tt&gt;. You can pass in all the
# same arguments to this method as you can to &lt;tt&gt;find(:first)&lt;/tt&gt;  If the first
# argument is an integer an array of the first n records will be returned.
#
# ==== Examples
#
# Person.first                                                  # Equivalent to Person.find(:first)
# Person.first(:conditions =&gt; [ &quot;user_name = ?&quot;, user_name])
# Person.first(5)                                               # Equivalent to Person.find(:all, :limit =&gt; 5)
# Person.first(5, :conditions =&gt; [ &quot;user_name = ?&quot;, user_name])</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Updated the docs for ActiveRecord#first and #last. Example for
#first below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;A convenience wrapper for &lt;tt&gt;find(:first, *args)&lt;/tt&gt;. You can
pass in all the&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;same arguments to this method as you can to
&lt;tt&gt;find(:first)&lt;/tt&gt; If the first&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;argument is an integer an array of the first n records will be
returned.&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;==== Examples&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Person.first # Equivalent to Person.find(:first)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Person.first(:conditions =&amp;gt; [ &quot;user_name = ?&quot;,
user_name])&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Person.first(5) # Equivalent to Person.find(:all, :limit =&amp;gt;
5)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Person.first(5, :conditions =&amp;gt; [ &quot;user_name = ?&quot;,
user_name])&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
